post_text:
Meet your Hampton FFA Vice President Rachel Rust!

What is your favorite part about being the FFA Vice President? My favorite part of being the Vice President is being able to work with my officer team and try and keep everyone in line.

What is a lesson FFA has taught you? A lesson that FFA taught me is that you don't have to be a farmer's son or daughter to be in FFA. And to also live in the moment.

What will you miss about FFA?I will miss working with my team and Mr.Miller. I am going to miss our lunch meetings every month and our group chats. I will miss seeing members show up to the meetings or events and being ready to do well or learn.
text:
Meet your Hampton FFA Vice President Rachel Rust!

What is your favorite part about being the FFA Vice President? My favorite part of being the Vice President is being able to work with my officer team and try and keep everyone in line.

What is a lesson FFA has taught you? A lesson that FFA taught me is that you don't have to be a farmer's son or daughter to be in FFA. And to also live in the moment.

What will you miss about FFA?I will miss working with my team and Mr.Miller. I am going to miss our lunch meetings every month and our group chats. I will miss seeing members show up to the meetings or events and being ready to do well or learn.

post_text:
Meet Your 2019-2020 Hampton FFA President Christian Eckhardt!

What is your favorite part about being the FFA President? My favorite part about being the FFA President is being able to help guide and teach those who are younger than me.

What is one life less that FFA has taught you? One life lesson FFA has taught me is you have family everywhere you turn. FFA is a banner that you identify with and you always know that when you see that blue denim jacket you are home.

What will you miss the most about FFA? What I will miss most about being an FFA officer is the people and the opportunities and events I was able to experience with every different person.
text:
Meet Your 2019-2020 Hampton FFA President Christian Eckhardt!

What is your favorite part about being the FFA President? My favorite part about being the FFA President is being able to help guide and teach those who are younger than me.

What is one life less that FFA has taught you? One life lesson FFA has taught me is you have family everywhere you turn. FFA is a banner that you identify with and you always know that when you see that blue denim jacket you are home.

What will you miss the most about FFA? What I will miss most about being an FFA officer is the people and the opportunities and events I was able to experience with every different person.
